#: sections/ai_rules.tex:3
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "\\addsection{Heroes}{\\skills/sorcery.png}"
msgid "\\addsection{AI rules}{\\skills/armorer.png}"
msgstr "\\addsection{Helden}{\\skills/sorcery.png}"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:6
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{2}\n"
"  AI rules apply to Enemy Heroes and all Combat encounters, including those against Neutral Units, in \\textbf{Solo Campaigns} and \\textbf{Cooperative} Scenarios.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\bigskip\n"
"  \\pagetarget{AI Units}{\\subheader{Combat against AI}}\n"
"  Foreword: these rules are intended to make fun challenging encounters, but still be simple enough to follow.\n"
"  You will likely find some loopholes which make the encounter too easy, but you may make AI behave more intellegently.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:13
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "These rules apply during Combat in \\textbf{Solo}\\index{Solo Mode} and \\textbf{Cooperative} Scenarios.  The rules for AI unit placement during setup are described in \\pagelink{CombatAISetup}{Combat chapter}."
msgid ""
"  The rules for AI unit placement during setup are described in \\pagelink{CombatAISetup}{Combat section}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Diese Regeln gelten während des Kampfes in \\textbf{Solo-}\\index{Solomodus} und \\textbf{kooperativen} Szenarien.\n"
"Die Bot-Regeln zur Einheiten-Platzierung vor einem Kampf sind im Kapitel \\pagelink{CombatAISetup}{Kampf} beschrieben."

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:15
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "When Neutral enemies or AI Heroes activate a unit, they follow a set of automatic instructions:"
msgid ""
"  When Neutral enemies or \\pagelink{AI Heroes}{AI Heroes} activate a unit, they follow a set of instructions:\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr "Wenn neutrale Feinde oder Bot-Helden eine Einheit aktivieren, folgen sie einer Reihe von automatischen Anweisungen:\\par"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\begin{itemize}\n"
"    \\item If it is an AI Hero, draw and resolve the next \\pagelink{AI Deck}{AI card}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:21
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Enemy Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} units prioritize attacking units of the \\textbf{same} tier.  If this is impossible, they attack the unit of a lower tier (in tier \\textbf{descending} order, down to bronze), and if that is also impossible, they attack the unit of a higher tier (in tier \\textbf{ascending} order)."
msgid ""
"    \\item Enemy Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} units prioritize attacking units of the \\textbf{same} tier.\n"
"    If this is impossible, they attack the unit of a lower tier (in tier \\textbf{descending} order, down to bronze), and if that is also impossible, they attack the unit of a higher tier (in tier \\textbf{ascending} order).\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Feindliche \\svg{unit_ground}- und \\svg{unit_flying}-Einheiten priorisieren Angriffe gegen Einheiten \\textbf{derselben} Stufe.\n"
"  Ist dies unmöglich, greifen sie Einheiten einer niedrigeren Stufe (\\textbf{in absteigender} Rangordnung runter bis Bronze) an, und wenn dies auch nicht möglich ist, greifen sie Einheiten einer höheren Stufe (in \\textbf{aufsteigender} Rangordnung) an.\\par"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:27
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\\textit{Example: \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground} has this priority: \\svg{golden} - \\svg{silver} - \\svg{bronze} - \\svg{azure}.}"
msgid ""
"    \\textit{Example: \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground} has this priority:\n"
"    \\svg{golden}\n"
"    - \\svg{silver}\n"
"    - \\svg{bronze}\n"
"    - \\svg{azure}.}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"  \\textit{Beispiel: \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground} haben diese Prioritäten:\n"
"  \\svg{golden}\n"
"  - \\svg{silver}\n"
"  - \\svg{bronze}\n"
"  - \\svg{azure}.}"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:30
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units prioritize attacking other Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units of the same tier, then lower tier, and finally higher tier, using the same tier order as above.  If there are no Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units for them to target, they prioritize Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} units in the same tier order."
msgid ""
"    \\item Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units prioritize attacking other Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units of the same tier, then lower tier, and finally higher tier, using the same tier order as above.\n"
"    If there are no Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units for them to target, they prioritize Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} units in the same tier order.\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\svg{unit_ranged}-Einheiten priorisieren andere \\svg{unit_ranged}-Einheiten derselben Stufe, dann die mit niedrigerer Stufe und zuletzt die mit einer höheren Stufe. Nutze dieselbe Rangordnung wie oben.\n"
"Wenn es keine \\svg{unit_ranged}-Einheiten als Ziel gibt, priorisieren sie \\svg{unit_ground}- oder \\svg{unit_flying}-Einheiten in derselben Rangordnung.\\par"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:41
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\\textit{Example: \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} has this priority: \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ranged} - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ranged} - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ranged} - \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying} - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying} - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying} - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}.}"
msgid ""
"    \\textit{Example: \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} has this priority:\n"
"    \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"    - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"    - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"    - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}.}\n"
"  \\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"  \\textit{Beispiel: \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} haben diese Prioritäten:\n"
"  \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"  - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"  - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"  - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}.}"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:44
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "In both cases, if there's more than one valid target, they attack the closest one.  If there's ever a tie between equally valid targets, the player chooses which unit is attacked."
msgid ""
"  In both cases, if there is more than one valid target, they attack the closest one.\n"
"  If there is ever a tie between equally valid targets, the player chooses which unit is attacked.\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"In beiden Fällen gilt: Gibt es mehrere gültige Ziele, greifen sie das Nächstliegende an.\n"
"Gibt es immer noch mehrere gültige Ziele, wählt der Spieler, welche Einheit angegriffen wird.\\par"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:46
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Enemy units cannot \\pagelink{Defend}{defend} unless instructed to."
msgid ""
"  Enemy units cannot \\pagelink{Defend}{defend} unless instructed to.\n"
"\n"
msgstr "Wenn nicht explizit aufgefordert, können feindliche Einheiten nicht \\pagelink{Defend}{verteidigen}."

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\pagetarget{AI Siege}{\\subsection*{AI Siege}}\n"
"  When the Walls and Gate are mentioned in Combat preparation but no additional information on how to arrange them is given, arrange them as a human player would:\n"
"  place the Gate in front of the \\svg{unit_ground} unit with the highest \\svg{initiative}.\n"
"  By default, the units do not attack the Walls -- they would rather fly over them to attack their target or move towards it through the Gate.\n"
"  If it is not possible, they take a \\pagelink{Defend}{Defend} Action.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:55
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\vspace{1em}\n"
#| "\\note{9}{In a siege against AI, the Arrow Tower follows the priority-rules like a Silver \\svg{silver} Unit. But if there are many valid targets, it cannot attack the nearest one, so it will attack the one that is closest to perishing (the smallest difference between \\svg{health_points-yellow} and current \\svg{damage-yellow}).}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"  The \\pagelink{Walls}{Arrow Tower} is treated like a Silver \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} unit.\n"
"  However, if it has multiple equally valid targets to attack, it will attack the one with the least health remaining (the smallest difference between \\svg{health_points} and current \\svg{damage}).\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\vspace{1em}\n"
"\\note{9}{In einem Belagerungskampf gegen Bots, folgt der Geschützturm den Prioritätsregeln einer Silber-Einheit \\svg{silver}. Bei mehreren gültigen Zielen kann er nicht die nächstliegende angreifen und wählt daher diejenige, die am stärksten beschädigt ist (also die kleinste Differenz zwischen \\svg{health_points-yellow} und aktuellem \\svg{damage-yellow} hat).}\n"
"\n"

