#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:139
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "AI Heroes use two Decks during Combat: the \\textbf{AI Deck}, and the \\textbf{AI Spell Deck}.  The AI Deck consists of three types of AI cards: Might \\svg[12]{might}, Magic \\svg{magic} and Skill \\svg{skill}.  Each Campaign Scenario lists the number and types of cards to include during setup.  Choose these cards \\textbf{randomly} when building the Deck.  If Skill cards are included, search for and set aside the Ability card related to it.  Build the \\textbf{AI Spell Deck} by separating the indicated Spells from the regular Spell Deck.  Shuffle these Decks during setup after building them."
msgid ""
"  AI Heroes use two Decks during Combat: the \\textbf{AI Deck} and the \\textbf{AI Spell Deck}.\n"
"  The AI Deck consists of three types of AI cards: Might \\svg[12]{might}, Magic \\svg{magic}, and Skill \\svg{skill}.\n"
"  Each Campaign Scenario lists the number and types of cards to include during setup.\n"
"  Choose these cards \\textbf{randomly} when building the AI Deck.\n"
"  Before each Combat, shuffle the AI Deck and its discard pile together.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Bot-Helden verwenden während des Kampfes zwei Decks: das Bot-Deck und das Bot-Zauberdeck.\n"
"Das Bot-Deck besteht aus drei Arten von Bot-Karten: Macht \\svg[12]{might}, Magie \\svg{magic} und Fähigkeiten \\svg{skill}.\n"
"Jedes Kampagnen-Szenario listet die Anzahl und den Typ der Karten auf, aus denen beim Spielaufbau das Bot-Deck gebildet wird.\n"
"Wähle diese Karten bei der Deckzusammenstellung \\textbf{zufällig}.\n"
"Wenn Bot-Fähigkeitskarten enthalten sind, suche nach den dazugehörigen Fähigkeitskarten und lege sie beiseite.\n"
"Bilde das \\textbf{Bot-Zauberdeck}, indem du die angegebenen Zaubersprüche vom normalen Zauberdeck trennst.\n"
"Mische diese Decks, nachdem du sie gebildet hast."

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:144
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "When an AI Hero \\textbf{activates} a unit, draw an AI card\\index{AI card} and follow its instructions before the unit moves and/or attacks.  If AI Deck is depleted during Combat, stop drawing from it.  The effect of each AI card depends on the game's \\pagelink{Difficulty}{Difficulty}.  The Might card \\svg[12]{might} is attached to the unit until the first respective attack/defense happens.  The AI Spell Deck is used whenever a Magic card \\svg{magic} is drawn.  If an AI Hero is instructed to draw a card, they will draw and resolve \\textbf{another card} from the AI Deck.  \\vspace*{\\fill} \\columnbreak \\pagetarget{AI Units}{\\subheader{Combat against AI}}"
msgid ""
"  When an AI Hero \\textbf{activates} a unit, draw an AI card\\index{AI card} and follow its instructions before the unit \\pagelink{AI Units}{moves and/or attacks}.\n"
"  If the AI Deck is depleted during Combat, stop drawing from it.\n"
"  The effect of each AI card depends on the game's \\pagelink{Difficulty}{Difficulty}.\n"
"  If an AI Hero is instructed to draw a card, they will draw and resolve \\textbf{another card} from the AI Deck.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Wenn ein Bot-Held eine Einheit \\textbf{aktiviert}, ziehe eine Bot-Karte\\index{Bot-Karte} und handle sie ab, bevor sich die Einheit bewegt und/ oder angreift.\n"
"Ziehe keine Karten mehr, wenn das Bot-Deck während des Kampfes aufgebraucht ist.\n"
"Der Effekt jeder Bot-Karte hängt vom \\pagelink{Difficulty}{Schwierigkeitsgrad} des Spiels ab.\n"
"Bot-Machtkarten \\svg[12]{might} werden an die Einheit angehängt, bis der/ die erste entsprechende Angriff/ Verteidigung erfolgt ist.\n"
"Das Bot-Zauberdeck wird verwendet, wenn eine Bot-Zauberkarte \\svg{magic} gezogen wird.\n"
"Darf ein Bot-Held eine Karte ziehen, dann ziehe eine weitere Karte vom Bot-Deck und handle sie ab. \\pagetarget{AI Units}{\\subheader{Kämpfe gegen Bots}}"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:148
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{AI Magic cards and AI Spell Deck}\n"
"  During setup find the Spells indicated in the Scenario and build the \\textbf{AI Spell Deck}.\n"
"  Before each Combat, shuffle the AI Spell Deck and its discard pile together.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  Whenever an AI Magic \\svg{magic} card is drawn, draw the next Spell from the AI Spell Deck and cast it.\n"
"  Discarded Spells go to its own AI Spell Discard Pile.\n"
"  If the AI Spell Deck empties before Combat ends, shuffle the AI Spell Discard Pile to form a new Spell Deck.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:156
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  The AI Spell Deck may contain more Spell cards than there are Magic cards in the AI Hero's Deck.\n"
"  This is intentional: not all Spells will be used during Combat.\n"
"  Some are included for the sake of variety.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:158
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  If the AI Hero is assigned a Spell card that is unavailable because it is in your Hero's Deck, and you do not have another copy, substitute it with a \\wikilink{spells/magic_arrow}{Magic Arrow} card.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:161
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  For certains Spells it can be unclear how the AI is supposed to cast them.\n"
"  See \\pagelink{AI Complex Spells}{Casting Complex Spells} for explanations.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:167
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{AI Skill cards}\n"
"  If Skill cards are included, search for and set aside the indicated card related to it (usually, an Ability).\n"
"  Whenever an AI Hero uses the AI Skill \\svg{skill} card, use the Skill card assigned to them in the Setup, but do not discard it afterwards.\n"
"  Contrary to the regular rules, the AI Hero can use the skill again, when instructed to do so by the AI Deck.\n"
"  Discard the AI Skill \\svg{skill} card as usual.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:169
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  AI Skill cards cannot be replaced, so if Scenario rules assign the AI Hero a card that your Hero has and you do not have another copy, remove that card from your Deck and \\textbf{Search (3)} the respective card's Deck to compensate your Hero for the loss.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:172
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{AI cards timing}\n"
"  After an AI card is resolved, discard it.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:176
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  The \\wikilink{ai\\#ai-cards}{Attack} Might \\svg[12]{might} card says about ``unit that is about to attack'', so if the currently activated unit doesn't have a valid target to attack, the Attack will apply to the next unit who is able to attack.\n"
"  Note that multiple unresolved cards can stack over successive activations.\n"
"  The same applies to any AI card which is not useful at the moment of drawing it.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  If an AI card increased a unit's \\svg{defense}, or triggered another card which increased it, the AI card stays attached to the unit until the first defense happens.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:181
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{AI Deck sharing}\n"
"  If there are multiple AI Enemy Armies in the Scenario, but the rules do not specify to which Enemy an AI Deck, an AI Spell Deck, or a Skill belongs, you should assume it is shared between them.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:188
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\bigskip\n"
"  \\bigskip\n"
"  \\pagetarget{AI Complex Spells}{\\subheader{Casting complex Spells}}\n"
"  In some Campaigns, enemies use Spells whose effects are not fully compatible with the standard use of AI Magic \\svg{magic} cards.\n"
"  To fully use their effects, here are extended descriptions of how AI Heroes should use each of these Spells.\n"
"  Scenarios can override these instructions.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:191
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{Spells attacking multiple targets}\n"
"  \\textit{Examples: \\wikilink{spells/fireball}{Fireball,} \\wikilink{spells/chain_lightning}{Chain Lightning.}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  When drawn, target any unit with one or two adjacent units from the player's army, prioritizing the groups where there are more higher-tier units.\n"
"  If there is more than one valid group, attack the one with the least health remaining (has the smallest difference between \\svg{health_points} and current \\svg{damage}).\n"
"  If there is still more than one valid target, you can choose which unit is attacked.\n"
"  If there are no player units adjacent to one another, target units that are not adjacent to any of the AI units.\n"
"  If that is also not possible, do not use this Spell -- instead, skip the AI \\svg{magic} card that activated this effect and put it on the bottom of the AI Deck, then shuffle this Spell back to the AI Spell Deck.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:200
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{Instant Defense Spells}\n"
"  \\textit{Example: \\wikilink{spells/stone_skin}{Stone Skin.}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:204
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  When drawn, put this card on the side of the Combat Board, then put a Defense Token on the unit with the highest \\svg{defense} to represent the card's effect -- it stays there until the Defense is resolved.\n"
"  If that unit already has a Defense Token, place it on the unit with the next highest \\svg{defense} instead.\n"
"  In case of a tie in \\svg{defense} value, give preference to the unit of the highest tier, then to the greatest value of \\svg{damage}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{Healing Spells}\n"
"  \\textit{Example: \\wikilink{spells/cure}{Cure.}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:210
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  When drawn, remove the \\svg{damage} from the AI unit with the greatest value of \\svg{damage} taken, starting with the highest tier available.\n"
"  If no AI unit has any \\svg{damage}, put the AI \\svg{magic} card that triggered the Spell at the bottom of the AI Deck, then shuffle this Spell card back to the AI Spell Deck.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:213
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{Single-round buffs}\n"
"  \\textit{Example: \\wikilink{spells/fire_shield}{Fire Shield.}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:217
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  When drawn, check the tier of the unit on which you are about to cast the Spell and count how many units of the same or higher tier there are on the Board.\n"
"  If more than half of those units have already activated this Round, do not cast the Spell; instead, set it aside and cast it when the first AI unit activates next Round; skip drawing the AI card for that activation.\n"
"  Multiple delayed Spells may accumulate and be cast during the same activation.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:220
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{Attack-weakening Spells}\n"
"  \\textit{Example: \\wikilink{spells/weakness}{Weakness.}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:223
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  When drawn, if the AI's activated unit is about to perform an attack that will provoke a Retaliation, cast this Spell on the Retaliating enemy to lower their \\svg{attack}.\n"
"  If the AI's unit causes no Retaliation, do not cast this Spell; instead, ignore the AI \\svg{magic} card that activated the Spell and put it at the bottom of the AI Deck, then shuffle the Spell card back to the AI Spell Deck."
msgstr ""
